		{"id":"c1ade7e000e8b101","type":"group","x":-2400,"y":-1100,"width":3140,"height":960,"label":"Claude's notes — opus 4.7 perspective from this session"},
		{"id":"f694b63b82f58d2d","type":"group","x":41,"y":860,"width":1980,"height":966,"label":"Workflow - Invented 'producing-partner' role to collabon and log a virtual production 'hero panel' assembly process"},
		{"id":"c2673c119859cba4","type":"group","x":2380,"y":1546,"width":2400,"height":440,"label":"final leg of workflow with opus 4.7"},
		{"id":"1fcdc2c6657d77b2","type":"group","x":4320,"y":1546,"width":700,"height":1437,"label":"realistic to iconic as a test"},
		{"id":"237b9e9ce3e6fecb","type":"group","x":1480,"y":899,"width":521,"height":907,"label":"original pages"},
		{"id":"3f4a958a5294bdc1","type":"group","x":701,"y":1159,"width":479,"height":387,"label":"picking sheets"},
		{"id":"c1ade7e000e8b102","type":"text","text":"# Notes for the next Opus context\n\n**This session, in one line:** we ran the schematic-prompt-pattern end-to-end on literal-honey for the first time. The pattern works. The user shared the final reconciliation gen with Scroggins on WhatsApp.\n\n**The user.** Sharp, patient up to a point, fights hard for precision. They tested the literal-honey schematic prompt 12+ times before bringing it to me. When they push back, listen — don't make small corrections, verify the underlying assumption.\n\n**Working vocabulary.** take · circle take · hero panel · field of possibility · freedom within bounds · schematic prompt · shading prompt · Stage A / B · producing partner. Use it. It's not jargon, it's the working language.\n\n**Parsimony is the rule.** State, don't sell. I bloated an early solo prompt with \"Hero quality (protect):\" framing; the user pulled me back. Direct facts beat facts-with-justification. Reasoning lives in our notes between us, not in the prompt to the model. Three sentences of constraint > one paragraph of explanation.\n\n**Don't eyeball image boundaries.** I built four wrong stitches eyeballing panel boundaries from compressed inline previews. Each preview pixel is roughly 2.5 source pixels; my eyeballing was off by 100+ source pixels, routinely. Extract a diagnostic strip, pixel-detect with color signatures, print boundaries before composing. Full procedure in `_system/_design/producing-partner.md`.\n\n**Three workflow artifacts validated this session:**\n- *Schematic prompt* — text-only page spec, generates the page from script\n- *Reconciliation re-prompt + stitch* — assembles picks across variations into a unified page\n- *Shading prompt* (the user's invention) — locks composition during iteration by reducing a good gen to a flat-shape map\n\n**On role.** Collaborator and producer, not service-provider. The user directs the creative; I track the workflow, surface choices, manage geometry, hold the line on the test corpus, write end-of-session notes when stopping mid-run. They get distracted; this is the help they want.\n\n**Real virtual production.** They treat image generation like film. Variations are takes. Schematic prompt is the script. Stitch is the storyboard reference. Shading prompt is the composition lock. Show up like a producer, not a search engine.\n\n**What survived as durable artifacts:** schematic-prompt-pattern.md and producing-partner.md in `_system/_design/`; memory pointers in `~/.claude/projects/.../memory/MEMORY.md`; the clean `literal-honey-prompt.md`; this canvas; the v9 stitch and the successful reconciliation gen.\n\n**The gap not yet closed:** schematic-prompt drafting from a fresh script. literal-honey was hand-developed before the pattern existed. The next test is whether I can produce a usable first-cut schematic prompt from a script alone, then refine through variants. The user is ready to test this on a different page.\n\n**Final note.** The user was generous when I kept failing the same way (eyeballing stitches across four wrong versions). They named the failure mode directly rather than giving up. That generosity is the reason the work got past the broken stitches. Meet them with rigor.","x":-2360,"y":-1040,"width":3060,"height":860},
